3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bluefin calculates funding rates every hour based on the premium/discount between the perpetual contract price and the underlying BNB spot price. Traders pay or receive funding based on their position direction when rates are positive (long pays short) or negative (short pays long). The exchange uses a time-weighted average price mechanism during the funding period to determine the final rate. Settlements occur automatically without requiring manual intervention, with funding amounts directly credited or debited from account balances."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","BNB","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BNB/USDT represents one of the highest volume trading pairs in crypto, making it ideal for funding rate arbitrage due to consistent rate fluctuations and deep liquidity. The pair's connection to the Binance ecosystem creates natural demand imbalances that generate profitable funding rate opportunities. Bluefin's position as the leading perpetual DEX on Sui provides early access to this emerging ecosystem while maintaining professional trading infrastructure."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BNB/USDT funding rates on Bluefin typically range from -0.1% to +0.3% per 8-hour period, with positive rates occurring approximately 65% of the time due to persistent long bias. During major BNB ecosystem announcements or BSC network upgrades, rates can spike to +0.5% or higher as speculative demand increases. The Sui blockchain's fast finality allows Bluefin to capture these rate movements more efficiently than traditional L1 DEXs. Rate volatility tends to increase during US trading hours and decrease during Asian sessions, creating predictable arbitrage windows."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bluefin's 1-hour funding settlements create 24 opportunities daily for rate arbitrage, significantly more than the standard 8-hour cycles on centralized exchanges. Cross-exchange arbitrage between Bluefin and major CEXs like Binance or OKX can yield 10-30 basis points per funding period during high volatility. The DEX's 0.02% maker fees and 0.05% taker fees are competitive with centralized alternatives while offering non-custodial trading. Delta-neutral strategies work particularly well on BNB/USDT due to the pair's high correlation with broader DeFi market movements."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Sui ecosystem risks include potential network congestion during high activity periods and smart contract vulnerabilities inherent to newer blockchain infrastructure. Bluefin's limited trading pairs mean reduced hedging options compared to established exchanges, potentially increasing basis risk during volatile periods. The DEX's relatively low overall volume can result in wider bid-ask spreads and increased slippage for larger position sizes. Funding rate arbitrage positions require constant monitoring due to the 1-hour settlement frequency and potential for rapid rate changes during market stress."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are BNB/USDT funding rates settled on Bluefin?","answer":"Bluefin settles funding rates every hour for all perpetual pairs including BNB/USDT. This provides 24 funding events per day, offering more frequent arbitrage opportunities compared to standard 8-hour cycles on centralized exchanges."},{"question":"What are the trading fees for BNB/USDT perpetuals on Bluefin?","answer":"Bluefin charges 0.02% for maker orders and 0.05% for taker orders on BNB/USDT perpetuals. These competitive rates make funding rate arbitrage strategies more profitable compared to higher-fee alternatives."},{"question":"Can I hedge BNB positions on Bluefin against other exchanges?","answer":"Yes, BNB/USDT positions on Bluefin can be hedged against spot holdings or perpetual positions on centralized exchanges. However, consider Sui network bridge times and potential basis risk when executing cross-exchange strategies."},{"question":"What makes Bluefin's BNB/USDT funding rates different from CEX rates?","answer":"Bluefin's 1-hour settlement cycle and Sui-based architecture create unique rate patterns compared to 8-hour CEX cycles. The DEX's growing but smaller user base can result in more pronounced rate deviations and arbitrage opportunities."}]}]
